e. This volume, the fourth of the eight-volume Strouse Edition, includes an informative historical introduction and illustrations, along with complete notes and scholarly apparatus, and is the definitive modern scholarly edition.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aHistoriography. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Historiography.2bisacsh1 aBossche, Chris Ramon Vanden, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarlyle, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVanden Bossche, Chris R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024250040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035509540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520355095423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520355095/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles